message.content:
cs.SI, cs.SOC, cs.IR, cs.DL, cs.DB

Reasoning: 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on analyzing the Facebook friendship graph and extracting relevant information about the distribution of relationships among subscribed users. 
- cs.SOC (Social and Behavioral Sciences) is also a likely category as the paper aims to understand underlying similarities between the development of OSN and real-life social networks. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is a possible category as the paper may use algorithms and tools provided by SNA to retrieve relevant information from the Facebook friendship graph. 
- cs.DL (Digital Libraries) is a possible category as the paper may discuss the collection and analysis of a significant sample of data reflecting relationships among subscribed users on Facebook. 
- cs.DB (Databases) is a possible category as the paper may discuss the storage and management of the data collected from the Facebook friendship graph.
